Trichocera annulata
is widespread in the Mediterranean region, with records from Algeria (
Edwards 1923
), Asia Minor and Ethiopia (
Dahl and Alexander 1976
), Malta (
Ebejer 2015
), Morocco (
Driauach et al. 2015
) and Sardinia (

Petrasiūnas
2009

). Along with our data from Mallorca, these records suggests that this species has an unusually high tolerance to warm temperatures within the genus 
Trichocera
.
